  <div class="wrap prose">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p class="lede">
      I'm a cloud security analyst. I govern cloud environments for a Fortune
      500 insurer, which mostly means secure configuration management and the
      automation around it.
    </p>
    <p>
      I came up through Lewis University's 4+1 program and a run of collegiate
      cyber competitions, which is where I learned that the interesting part of
      security is never the exploit. It's whether the thing was built so the
      exploit had somewhere to go.
    </p>
    <p>
      Outside work I run a homelab like it's production. The projects on this
      site are where I keep the same instinct sharp: build it, break it, back it
      up, and prove the backup restores.
    </p>

